,Recommended,263060,15601530,"Posted: 28 April, 2015",all,Skorly,I can make a knife skin without paying 300$.....10/10
76561198146292727,Recommended,263060,19814749,"Posted: 20 December, 2015",all,ScaRy,"This is among the best games I've had the pleasure of playing, hands down.It's a shame this game doesn't get the attention it deserves. There's a small, yet loyal following that genuinely wants this game to be the best it can be. Even though it's a voxel-based FPS, it far exceeds your run-of-the-mill CoD or BF in many aspects. It's the simplicity of Blockstorm that makes it beautiful.What's great about this game is amount of customization available through the in-game editor. You can create your own knife skins, guns, mechas, player models, and can even forge your own maps with ease. Because of this, there's a ton of free community-created content via the Workshop. You don't have to sell your house, car, and your left testicle for a knife skin like you would in CS:GO. Just subscribe to an item in the Workshop, and you're good to go.There is one main criticism I would give this game: The ping. If I had a lamborghini for everytime I shot someone in the face without them dying, I would be Tai Lopez. It's not uncommon to see pings above 150. It can be frustrating dying to someone you KNOW you should have killed. This is one of the reasons why this game may never be competitively viable. However, you'll learn to shrug it off and keep playing. It's still a blast to play!For the price of a burger, you just can't beat it. Skip food for a day. Buy this game."
,Recommended,263060,32632826,Posted: 21 June,all,The Grey Raven,"This game may be easily seen as a Minecraft style shooter that tries to get popular from this tactic, and as such it could make you think it has nothing to offer. This can obviously stimulate people to ignore it or read reviews skeptically. If you are reading this, you either probably want to get this game or think you may want to. I am going to tell you what this game really is and why you may want to spend your time in Blockstorm.Blockstorm is obviously indeed a Minecraft with guns scenario, though the features this game brings are much more than you would expect. You can find most of these nowhere else. Here are my pros. This game has a very in depth editor for every single visual element in the game. Whatever you see here you can make look different and as such personalize it for yourself or others depending on what you want your role to be in this community. These visual elements include weaponry, edited based on class, (such as making an assault rifle or knife skin), maps, characters, and even NPCs. Each of these are produced in an also voxel based editor with small blocks used to make them. Next, all of the maps in the game are fully destructible minus forcefield blocks. This and the weapon editor makes everything in the game extremely dynamic, to a level of Battlefield if not more. For example, say you are on an oil rig. You walk up a building to shoot two people on a bridge battling. You pull out your nyan cat rocket launcher and begin aiming at your prey. You easily realize Big Smoke and that Spetznaz guy aren't going to enjoy this. The rocket is fired, blowing the entire bridge up and making it fall into the water to be gone the entirety of the match.Now for the much smaller list of my cons. Blockstorm is faced with the extremely unfortunate lack of funding. The creators are led by IndieGala, who no longer pay GhostShark for this game's development. This means since the game wasn't popular to begin with, it certainly began to lose the little steam it had to begin with. Fortunately though, there are still 156 and counting dedicated players in this community, and they are here to stay. This means that the community is more connected, which may not be seen as a con to some people. Also, as you can't sprint, grenades can be op in this game. This is an issue that can be avoided, though not easily sometimes. It seems to appear in this game that it has a lower ping refresh rate, so people won't get hit sometimes in higher ping servers.Overall, this game has immesurable dynamisism, and a dedicated community for all the fps needs you should have, regardless of its numbers and other minor development bugs. Thank you for reading this, I hope it helped you decide."
,Recommended,263060,15936074,"Posted: 21 May, 2015",all,RTL Das Familiengericht,"Well well well. This game in short is Ace of Spades revived with a big focus on gameplay along the lines of Counter Strike 1.6 and Half Life 1 Multiplayer. It really is great fun and the graphics kind of give it a charm that makes it feel like it comes straight out of 1998 or something. The block based levels are great, giving you tons of ways to play a match for example literally pumping a 100 bullet mag into a wall just so other people don't have the cover of said wall anymore. Of course you can also place blocks yourself, building small walls to crouch behind when you reload.Basicly if you like Counter Strike-ish games with a little twist this sure is a game to pick up, especially now when its on sale.And the editor where you can make maps, skins for your weapons and for your characters isamazing. Easy to use for everyone and so many options to be creative with. I bet this is where most people will spend their time."
76561198026239755,Recommended,263060,24508079,"Posted: 24 July, 2016",all,mayancal3ndar,"I moved from Robocraft and got this instead. The major pros about this game is that the weapons are well-balanced, but what would be great if the Sniper Rifle were like the AWP from CS: Source and harder to use, because campers have it easy. Anyways, the other pro is the speed of the combat; it's not too slow like CS:GO, but not too fast like Quake. But a neutral point about this game is the lack of players; give it some attention! But a negative about this game is.... hard to come up with.9.5/10 because of the very small amount of annoying players that I have seen. The playerbase is like a box of Crayola brand crayons: creative and non-toxic. Honestly, give this game more players."
,Recommended,263060,23467212,"Posted: 9 June, 2016",all,Furball,"Ok, let’s get this review started. For those of you that want a brief overview (or those of you that can't be stuffed reading the massive review below), there is a pros/cons list down underneath the actual review.PROSFirst good thing is that the game has a weapon, player model, and map maker, which is rather nice, as it brings a personal touch to the game.Second good thing is It has workshop support which is also quite nice.Third, is the pretty decent game-play, although the lag is a mild problem, its mainly due to the horrible internet where I live.Another upside is the balanced weapons.And the fifth and likely most important upside, is the completely destructible environments that don't take a beast of a computer to run.Next, there is the sixth good thing...the MECHS...Completely awesome and deadly, those things tear through almost anyone in their path. They take a fair few missiles to bring down too.On a final point, you can create your own servers quickly and easily.CONSFirst off, the editors are rather limited. The gun and player model editor are ridiculously frustrating with the editor being unable to remove most blocks from both gun and player model is infuriating. I could understand if it was a single block in the middle of the gun or at the back, however unfortunately you cant remove half the gun and/or the middle layer...for unexplained reasons. On top of that, the size of editing space is incredibly limited, only allowing you to place one or two blocks in any direction outside of the original gun, which makes it extremely frustrating if you are trying to make your machine gun look like the heavy lancer from Ratchet and Clank 2...Not sure how many people remember that game...ANYWAY, back to the review. On to the map editor. The editor is relatively less limited, however the inability of placing very many NPC's in a small area is annoying to say the least when trying to create a zombie survival. Another downside is that the map editor can at times be borderline confusing with what is considered the actual map, and what isn't.The second downside is that-despite the weapons being balanced, there simply aren't enough to make the game feeldifferent from most other shooters.The third downside is that other than an A.I for turrets and zombies, there are no bots.The fourth downside is that you have to be online to play, even to just test an edited map or piece of equipment.LIST OF PROS AND CONSPROS-Mostly balanced weapons-Decent game-play-Bi-pedal mechanical walkers (Giant walking things with a minigun, rocket launcher and what seems to be a power-fist :P)-Editors-for the personal touch that you need while mass-murdering everyone in your path with a bright orange machine-gun while looking like a storm trooper..,-Workshop support so you can upload your creations and make use of what other's have uploaded. Useful for doing what is mentioned above :P-You can make your own server and watch as it fills up with random players from around the globe :PCONS-Editors are extremely limited-but have good potential.-Not enough weapons...(THERE CAN NEVER BE TOO MANY WEAPONS...well..most of the time)-No A.I/Bots (except zombies/turrets)-Online play only-no editing maps and playing them offline.And finally, dear reader, you stumble in relief over what is known as a summary :PSo, decent shooter at its core, but it needs a lot of modification with the editors, as well as requires actual A.I to fight against offline. I'd personally recommend buying it on sale.Thats all for this review. Dragon out."
,Recommended,263060,16208978,"Posted: 5 June, 2015",all,PrudentTorture,10/10 better than ace of spades.
,Recommended,263060,15528589,"Posted: 24 April, 2015",all,optimuswhat,"This game is pretty fun!Imagine Ace of Spades, except actually improved upon and not turned into a Call of Duty-like game. It features a variety of weapons and interesting mechanics. I think one of the big sellers of the game is its custom weapon and playerskin makers, as well as map making system. The combat is fairly good, though it has room for improvement. I found that matches tend to be rather... Quiet. It felt somewhat isolated when playing with other players. Hopefully the community grows to circumvent this issue.The loadout system is very interesting. There's a weight (In KG) system that dictates how fast you move. If it's 6 KG, you move pretty fast. If you weigh 10 KG, you'll be slower.There's weapons like a rifle, a sniper rifle, an assault rifle, an SMG, a shotgun, and a heavy machine gun. They all tend to synergize well with a certain side-arm. Yes, there's more than just your pistol. You're given the choice between choosing a regular pistol, uzi, and a small shotgun with two shells loaded in. Ontop of that, you can also pick your grenade type. It can be a frag grenade, a C4 that can be detonated on command, a claymore that detonates when a player touches its laser, or a freakin' RPG... With only one rocket.You can also use a block placing tool and a shovel to manipulate the terrain.A few issues I have encountered is that the game does NOT autosave your custom skins, maps, characters, etc. This means if you accidentally quit, it's gone. Yes, it happened to me when I was least expecting it. Another issue that I feel like only I get annoyed by is making weapon skins. Whenever you make a weapon skin, there's certain blocks that cannot be broken. This is so that you don't make an SMG look like a shotgun. I tend to get a little annoyed with it, but I can understand why it's there. I would like if there was some system that lets you delete those blocks, but on the offset that only you can see the skin. The only other issue is that the community is small. Hopefully by the end of the two week free-to-play event, the community would had grown by then.Other than that, it's pretty good. Get it if you liked the original Ace of Spades. Cheers for monthly updates!"
