,Recommended,263060,26181023,"Posted: 23 October, 2016",all,Sweep,"About BlockstormBlockstormis a first person shooter made with blocks, and a highly detailed editor that let's you make just about anything you can think of, It's extremely fun and one of the best I've played in a long time, make sure to read this review as every game does have some negatives Though very little, and at the end of the review I'll send you a link to where you can actually get this game for free, so let's just get straight into the pros and consGameplayAs I said above it's a traditional first person shooter, with the regular things you would expect to see, and like most of them it all works out really well though it added some new features like the shovel, and a block adder, during any kind of matches you can dig into the environment and build on it, allowing you to build cover or make unique breaches into enemy territory, overall the main gameplay of the game for me is ok, as most of my hours in the game aren't in multiplayerThe EditorIn the game you can use a thing called editors where you can build on or edit any model in the game including weapon skins, characters, mechs, and maps, this feature allows you to make highly detailed creations of nearly anything you want that can be instantly used in gameplay, you can also upload these creations to the workshop and have others use/download your item, by the time this review is out I’d have made about 17+ workshop items for the game, the creation factor is very easy to learn and really fun once you master it, and it’s so fun that almost all of my hours in the game have gone to making things rather than even playing it.All in All Blockstorm is a really nice first person shooter with many features!9/10 From MeSweep"
