,Not Recommended,263060,22854174,"Posted: 7 May, 2016",all,CHASER4G,"Blockstorm is a voxel FPS that has a wonderful system but with poor gameplay quality.Blockstorm is unique. Players have nearly 100% freedom in designing their own character, equipment and even maps. Designes can be shared through Steam Workshop, in which others simply need to click 'Subscribe' in order to download the designs and use it for their own.However, these are the only things that attracts me to this game.The gameplay itself is boring as ♥♥♥♥.Currently, there are only RPG, LMG, MP5, AK, UZI, Shotgun, Sniper, rifle and handguns in which all of these have horrible sound effect and it makes you feel like you're using a card board gun made in China.Character actions are basic and you are only limited to aim-shoot, run, crounch and jump. No sprinting, diving, or lying on the ground. If you want to play Super Mario in 3D, this game is for you.Grenades are ♥♥♥♥ing annoying in this game. Each players are supplied with 2 grenades every spawn and this makes the match into a grenade dodgeball where players throw their grenade before they shoot when they see an opponent.Knifes are also one slice kill with zero sound effect where it makes you feel like you're cutting through tofu.The only unique part about the game play is that the blocks are destructable, and it is interesting seeing the battlefield constantly change its shape and how players must move differently according to the change.But remember, the rest is total sh!t.The only hope to enjoy this game is to use most of your time designing and if you are want a good gameplay experience, I recommend you to bring your friends.Overall:Good concept but lack of polishing.I understand that the game community is not big yet and the devs do not have a large income from this game, but this is my honest impression of this game at its current state."
