,Not Recommended,263060,12076404,"Posted: 12 September, 2014",all,Grester,"After reading the reviews implying this was the follow up of Ace of Spades and Guncraft (GC) I got interested in buying the game since I was a big fan of Guncraft. Oh boy was I fooled.Not much more alive than GC - except during sales (but that happens in any game) or DEMO servers (which like the name says, it has demo players) - and with gameplay similar or worse than GC I've felt completely tricked by those reviews.While in GC most people still had the patience to make their own gun just for their own sake/fun, I doubt here anyone will waste time making a full scale playermodel since the developers made like 25 of them. And since it doesn't have gun maker did they compensate with more standard weapons? Nope, I believe it has even less standard guns than in GC himself. Sure it has the basic weapon types (assault rifle, shotgun, sniper rifle, machine gun), but personally the only gun I find effective is the machine gun.Without mentioning that layout management enforces you to ""run"" (there's no sprinting) overcombered in a game that you ""GOTTA GO FAST"". Each gun/tool has a certain weight. The heavier you are, the slower you ""run"". This means either you like it or not you'll always have to ""run"" with things you may not use in the match. But even if you did carry a rocket launcher or more combersome weapons, would it make a diference? Nope because you'd be running extremely slow.Also has a map maker that nobody will have enough time to make anything good.It kinda made me depressed waste 12€ on such game. As if that wasn't enough 2 weeks later the game gets a weekend sale for 5€. In times like this you wish steam would make refunds. (At the time of purchase steam didn't had refunds yet).If you bought the game, hope you enjoy selling your cards. If you haven't but still feel inclined to try it out, get the demo and play on the populated demo servers (the non-demo are empty). Unlike the game description says, you can play 2 gamemodes and like 5 maps. Or just do family share with a friend.Pro tip: If you reload a weapon you can switch to another one while the other finishes reloading (switching weapons doesn't stop reload)."
