,Recommended,263060,25045852,"Posted: 20 August, 2016",all,linuxpunk,"Average Voxel Shooter + Good Skin CreatorBlockstorm is 2 games in one. On one hand, you got an average, not particullary interesting voxel FPS, on the other hand you got a good interface to create skins for characters, items and creating maps. The good side, anyone can make a skin, the bad side, ANYONE can make a skin. If you where looking for a Achan shooter, a 9gag counterstrike clone, look no further. Every and any meme ever posted already has a skin: Pepe, Sonic, Dat Boi, Pedo Bear, AWESOME, there's even a nyan cat rocket launcher. There's also a pink uniform Hitler with his junk showing I wish I could unsee.The FPS gameplay is average. It plays a little like Counterstrike in that headshots are a sure kill, but you can stomach a few body shots. It has quite a few different game modes, DM, TDM, CTF, zombies, and Assault (one team assaults the other defends). Everything is destroyable and you have building blocks like in all minecraft clones. Other than that, the physics suck.The variety of weapons is actually very small, you have ONE assault rifle, ONE sniper rifle, ONE machinegun, ONE pistol, two shotguns and two SMG, but only because they can be used as primary or secondary. It has endless skins, which makes up for the lack of variety, but it doesn't matter if the assault rifle looks like a kalashnikov or a candy cane, it will play the same.Also on the bad side, the character skins don't have a first person render, only the guns, so you only get to see the skin you choose when you are killed or if you win the game (cool victory pose for the 3 top players).I can't say this is the best FPS out ther, but it's ok for it's price (bought it on sale, though). If you want to create skins or maps, this is a great and easy to learn tool.I appreciate Linux support."
