,Recommended,263060,34404980,Posted: 21 August,all,✪ H1tScAn_LΣO9999 ✪,"So, Blockstorm is a nice voxel arcade FPS, the kind that used to be common in 2014. It's one of the few italian games to actually be nice. So, let's stop talking and discuss thePROS+Good game balance: Weapons are pretty well balanced between each other.+Weapons are few, but fill all the needed roles. There's a gun for everything, even if the weapons are less than your usual FPS. This actually makes it easier to understand each weapon and encourages competitive play.+Simple, clean HUD. Tells you everything you need, without being too fancy and clutter the screen with useless stuff.+Very good surround audio. The sounds may not be the best ones, but sure as hell stereo saved my life plenty of times. Footsteps are the key.+Easy to learn, extremely hard to master.+Simple, light to run graphics show you only what really matters, and as such it will be easy to get your friends on the game.+Custom SkinsBlockstorm has it's fair share of pros... But there are alsoCONS-Custom Skins (yes, it's both a + and a -, as it hinders competition)-Some weapons could use a little more balancing. Guns are well balanced... But some of them could still use some tweaking, seeing how the pistol is useless.-Inconsistent hits. Yes, you really don't feel like hitting the enemy. He wont flinch, he won't really bleed, just a barely visible splurt of cubic blood after every shot. Makes it a bit hard to tell when the enemy has been hit, and the hitmarkers are hard to see(illuminating crosshair)-Inconsistent explosives: the explosive weapons are really awkward and bipolar, sometimes you get a rocket in the face and survive to get your revenge, sometimes a grenade lands really far (and even behind a wall!) and you die instantly.-Tracers: They are there just for show, and won't really show the actual shots you're firing: the actual hitscans are MUCH more accurate than what the tracers show.-Not really a development fault, but the game is slowly dying. There are still a lot of people playing, but i feel like it won't last long...------------------------VerdictBlockstorm is a simple, catchy shooter. It could still use some improvements, but the devs seemingly stopped worrying about this game. Anyhow, the major bugs are fixed and the experience is mostly bug free.Score: 8.1/10"
