,Recommended,263060,12287502,"Posted: 29 September, 2014",all,Daza_NZ,"Blockstorm is a fun game and what makes this game great is its map editor and avatar editor. The editor not only allows you to create a map but you can also create your own prefabs (objects, walls, props etc and add it to your prelab library) but you can download new ones from the community and also share your own creations as well and of course your maps. The map editor is quite powerful, you can easily copy complete objects big or small to duplicate including very large buildings. This makes things like creating roads or wanting to duplicate multiple objects easy.  If you want to cut your teeth on designing good multiplayer maps this is it. There could be some minor tweaks and polish added to the editor to improve its ease of use but its not hard to learn and does the job well.I'm impressed with how there are no frps drops from some of the detailed and large maps some of the community (some good quality maps there) has made for an older computer like mine.At the moment there is only 3 game modes but more is to come. For where Blockstorm is now its well worth the money, if you like designing stuff then you probably will spend just as much time in the editor as playing online. The thing this game lacks at the moment is more players. No doubt we will see more weapons and gameplay being added in future updates."
,Recommended,263060,11444929,"Posted: 27 July, 2014",all,get outta here,"This is a list of things about Blockstorm, I've noted some of the things I've noticed and liked/disliked. Now do understand that everything i've listed, as said by the devs, is subject to change in the game. You can check the date of this review if you find something off.Pros:-Nice gunplay, and most of the guns are very nicely balanced.-Graphics are very good for a voxel-based game.-Fun to mess around with the ingame character/map editer (You can literally make Elmo if you wanted).-No lag on official servers-Good netcode that doesn't cause lag issues-Freedom of choice (in term's of loadout,looks, ect).-Very nicely made official maps/ characters.-Very active and kind devs.Cons:-If you lag, it benefits you(I hope for a fix ASAP, or even a ping limit setting whenever you make a match)-On some maps, it's very easy to block a spawn and camp. (This can definitly be fixed).-Knife is a bit overpowered imo (I can see backstabs as 1 hit kills).(I've decided this was unecessary)-Building on the battlefield could use a bit of improving (Have a ghost block, be able to build on a face you can't see, besides this, building is nice).-Very small community (It really bugs me)-A bit of tank controls (Would LOVE to see it more tight)(it's been adjusted to be more tight)What I think could be added to enhance the game:-Sandbox/lounge gamemode: You can just build and hang out with friends or anyone and show off that awesome skin you just got finished making if you wanted.-Thirdperson Spectator and/or a Spectator team-Server modding or modding: Could be used to allow people to create their own gamemodes (ex. RP)-Custom Weapons (and possibly edit the stats)-Workshop support(it's been implemented. YAY)Edit: I've noticed a lot of discussions based around on whether or not this game is different from Ace of Spades, Guncraft, and any other voxel shooter out there. And I, as a reviewer, should set an answer to a potential game loss. This game does stand on it's own in it's own right.Yes, it takes certain elements from AOS, but don't always think it rips off. Blockstorm was likely inspired by AOS, and it adds onto what AOS had done, though doing it in it's own way.Yes, the shooting may be a bit generic, but it can be very tactical if you play with the right people. The game was designed to be a bit slow paced, almost like Battlefield.Anyone who is against this game, whether by similarities with the other voxel shooters, I do hope you give it a chance as it's own title. It's nowhere near as terrible as some have said, but rather good.And besides, it's in Early Access. It may improve, it may setup or add, it IS changing whether you like it or not, possibly for the better or even worse.To conclude...This game is something you could pick up and enjoy on the spot (For me it was). Being able to create your own character in ANY way you wanted to is something that makes this cake shine. I also enjoy making maps, as the editer is very good. And currently with a price tag of $12(It may change), it's cheaper and better than the $15 AOS."
