76561198066436824,Recommended,263060,23621180,"Posted: 17 June, 2016",all,The Flying Toaster,"I’ll be honest in saying that When I installed Blockforce I felt it was going to be some generic “Minecraft Shooter” that flooded steam a while back, and in fact it’s mechanics are generic to some degree. The gunplay is based on loadouts of equipment that vary in power, and weight/speed. You can dig, and place blocks to shape the environment to your advantage, while competing with the enemy in objective game modes, and or deathmatch. So far, so generic. But when playing the actual game, I found a fine game that can give you a good time if you want to play a destructive shooter with in game tools to make your own fun.The customization tools to visually alter your own guns, melee , power ups, and player models. helps personalize the game for the creative while keeping the distinctive sounds, and stats of each gun to avoid balance issues. The tools themselves are fun, and easy to use to create your gun models. from the simple melee weapon to your own full character models, and if all else fails, you can reskin the RPG pink in about 10 clicks.You can also Build maps as well, something the workshop has used to make many things. The map editor is almost exact like the gun editor. but with pickups, and blocks with varying durability. and environmental editing to layout the map of your creation. But with The dozens of strange, and fun Workshop Maps, and the abstract beauty of the “Built in” maps. You’ll have so many maps to Discover, Download, Drop in, and Demolish.A game, that has still got some servers kicking (As of 6/17/2016) and is a fine time with creative friends who could use a diet of destruction based sub arena shooting, with an surprisingly good looking set of maps to utterly destroy. And if what they give you isn’t cutting it, the workshop, and your own hands can make something."
