,Recommended,263060,22129663,"Posted: 29 March, 2016",all,『TheAwkwardCoder』,"*MAY 2016 VERSION*I would have to say, I actually like this game. A lot.Parts of the community are decent, and as long as you can find the right people, you can learn how to play pretty quickly.Although, one of the only complaints I have about it for now is that the Hunt matches could use more maps. Currently it's only the infested map, and it gets a bit boring after a while to be able to play Hunt on only one map. Other than that, it's a pretty great game! Especially when you see the workshop content! All the awesome player and weapon skins, quite a few people have contributed to this game's greatness! And finally, I will get down to it.Pros:Decent CommunityA great amount of workshop contentThere is at least 1 server active a day6 guns that are all special in their own wayYou can literally just run around and knife peopleKill Deadpool as a duck with a Steam Sale RPGYou can literally have a stick thin gunBlowing up everything is funThe fact that you don't pay for new skins, and still have CS:GO skinsCons:Some parts of community are a bit iffy than the restIf you suck at aim, you will suck at the game (not guarenteed)The spawnkilling techniques of some players, ripThe fact that there's only one map for HuntSo yeah, that's my review on the game. Still though, the spawnkills.*UPDATE: MAY 2017*Well, it's been about a year since I reviewed this game, so I figured I should update my review.As the community currently stands, I've been playing more active than I have a year ago, and...Well, a lot of players who were helpful, active, or high-ranked players, have seemed to completely abandoned this game by this point. It's pretty rare to see anybody above lvl 90 join a server, ever, except on weekends or during random games with 6 or more people. The majority of players are either lvl 1's, scattered levels between 2-50, and the lvl 70's. Although, this remaining small portion of the community can be divided into seperate groups.Group 1: New players that are completely silent, either not knowing how to talk or choosing not to. This silent group also applies to some higher level players, who don't speak much.Group 2: The remaining bad part of the community. Either people who spam gg ez in your face all the time or complain about other people being bad, they don't come up too often but you do see them in games. Most of these people will complain that it's a dead game, which in my opinion leads to the question: Then why are you even playing a game you don't believe in? Are you serious?Group 3: The relatively ideal players, these players will chat occassionally, or often, possibly supply supportive information, or come up with some interesting chat topics as you stalk each other on the maps. Sometimes you can even arrange events between yourselves, such as limiting everybody to a certain weapon and providing some occassionally fun times. Although they are decently rare, you'll still see them, and they will provide some of the best times in this game. All of my good memories about this game come from these people, they MAKE the game realtively fun, absolutely.Skins are still being made daily for this game, so the steam workshop support is still going strong. Overall, your purchase of this game is kind of relative. The times this game is most active will always be on the weekends, since the community likes to hold events during the weekend. That is, the active parts of the community. Ultimately, it depends on whether you can spare some money for this game. I would never reccomend buying the full price for this game, especially in its current state. $7 for this game would be an absolute bad deal for the experience you desire, just wait for a sale on this. This game goes on sale often, so you should be able to grab a copy if you don't already have one. For $1, I would reccomend this game as a cheap multiplayer alternative. However, if you want games with higher player counts, or playing with different people, I would not reccomend this game. Most likely with this game, you'll be playing mostly the same people, over and over again, with some newcomers inbetween. Overall, depends on your patience, whether you want to play with the literal same people only, and if you desire higher server counts.(I'm biased from previous experiences, so I still give this game a reccomendation.)"
