,Recommended,263060,18945461,"Posted: 7 November, 2015",all,MichaelPCgamer,"This game runs very smooth.  Unlike other modern FPS games, which run poorly on my PC, this game runs well when all graphics and resolutions are at absolute lowest.  Which means turning EVERYTHING low and off.The gameplay itself is similar to Counter Strike and Warface and many other vs games that include capture the flag, team deathmatch, and storm-like games.  Despite the graphics not looking real (more like minecraft), the game still looks good and the gameplay is smooth and interesting.One of the things this game may need, in the future, is a single-player campaign.  Like Counter Strike and Warface, which will have a campaign, this game needs one to expand its gameplay.Like someone else said in their review, there needs to be a way to allow two or more players to collaborate their ideas into one map or gun to lower time spent and to make the map or gun out of two or more different ideas.The guns in this game need work.  Just because you can customize your weapon, doesn't mean they WORK differently.  There need to be more gun types and accessories added, especially on the sniper rifles.This is one of the few games that I know of where you can literally destroy the entire map.  With a team of about 10 - 12 compliant players, you COULD destroy the entire map and allow for NO room for spawning.I recomend this game to anyone who is into regular casual FPS games like minecraft with guns.  The servers can also be reached from different places such as at home, outside in internet providable places, and even at school.  This is important because I used to mainly play this game at school to pass by time.  I give this game 4.5 stars."
