,Recommended,263060,10787631,"Posted: 25 June, 2014",all,zero,"I absolutely love this game!PRO'S:The map creator and the character creator are both equally fun to use and very innovative.The gameplay and/or gunplay is amazing andsatisfying, the gun balance is incredibly well-done.Controls are simple but really familiar, being  similar to Counter-Strike and other voxel-based shooters.The graphics in this game are actually quite great, including features like Anti-aliasing, dynamic shadows, bloom and lens flares.Game performance for an early access game is incredible, no stuttering and no frame-drops at no times during gameplay. Blockstorm uses the Unity engine, which is known to be a very well-known engine and many of the games we know and love have been built using the same engine Blockstorm uses. Don't forget that the Unity engine allows the devs to create ports for their games so I expect Blockstorm to expand onto Mac OSX and Linux in the near future.CON'S:Lack of people playing. I know this isn't the game's fault for this as you can see throughout my review, but the game has a few number of people playing everyday, peaking at around maybe 20 people online playing the game. Here's theofficial charts.Overall, Blockstorm is an simple, yet fun to play game and I would recommend it to anyone who loves a good shooter.My advice if you enjoy the game, spread the word across your friends, our community we have here as Steam, tell them that this game is a well-done and a enjoyable game, this amazing game needs to be heard across the whole internet so we have more people playing and enjoying this.Thank you for reading, I hope my efforts will improve upon the game."
