,Recommended,263060,11015445,"Posted: 2 July, 2014",all,MedievalSwagger,"Some may look at this game as another childish block based ""MineCraft"" style shooter.When in reality, it's just an incredibly fun and user friendly multiplayer shooter experience. This game easily gives you a creative outlet, which makes the game so much more personally AND conceptually. Instead of buying $14.99 DLC for a few new maps for your AAA titles, you can find a new server that is hosting brand-new community created and free maps that are incredibly fun. The diversity and variety between the maps creates more memorable and fun moments than you would even hope to experience in games like CounterStrike, or Call of Duty.The ability to create your own character from the very pixel, allows anyone who desires it to express themselves in anyway they want. There are no limits, or restrictions to your creativity. You don't just have a few different generic military themed outfits to pick like Call of Duty or a few character models like CS:Source, And if we haven't learned anything, it's that You, the player, loves customization. Why else do you buy camos off the market or aim for the head as much as you do in Call of Duty?The game is currently in early access, and is only going to get better. This game needs a lot of support, and needs to be brought out of the dark. The potential is amazing and it is a shame that more people aren't playing this game. I have a few pretty fancy AAA titles in my library, but this Indie game that isn't even finished yet draws my attention more than anything else in my library of games.If you are to buy this game, you will enjoy it. It's very fun with friends, and the possibilities are endless with the amount of customization. I bought a 4-pack for my friends and we love to join up in the same server and play."
,Recommended,263060,11076311,"Posted: 4 July, 2014",all,TheargoDarkness,"Game Rating - 4.5/5PROS -+Destruction is epic.+Weapons feel good.+Character and map customization are fantastic features.+Slick and friendly menu UI.+Responsive and active developers.CONS -+Player base is small. (for now)This game is great! Player customization, destruction, and gun-play is the heavy focus in this minecraft-inspired FPS. The developers allow for the player to be as deep or simple with customization. The customization tools are fairly easy to get the hang of. Destruction is something that is far underused in video games today. I can safely say that Block Storm does destruction justice. Walls will explode and crumble as you fire upon them. Buildings will fall to the ground if there is no support. The map becomes a wasteland by the end of the match. The gun-play in this game is executed very well. Players are not difficult to see or shoot on the battlefield because the models of the players in-game are the perfect blend of block and realism. Overall, Blockstorm is a breath of fresh air in the FPS genre.RATING - 4.5/5"
76561197977820099,Recommended,263060,10744396,"Posted: 24 June, 2014",all,Lizzard,"There ae a lot of questions that come up with this game, so let me keep this introduction brief. If you're like me, you've probably played several of these Early Access/Beta games and have been burned a few times by lack of content and general poor quality. Some I like (Prison Architect, Project Zomboid, Space Engineers), others I've quickly forgotten about. This is a game that makes the former list and will continue to recieve my support.For some background, you shold familiarize yourself with a couple of other games- Minecraft (everyone knows of); Silent Storm (A tactical 3rd person RTS that has a fully destructable environemnt); The Battlefield games; King Arthur's Gold.This game combines elements of each of those previous games and does most of it better than similar titles.The resolution: It's a higher quality than Minecraft and in general, the graphics are a better quality than most Voxel games like it. If you blow up a block, for instance, the block explodes into dozens of smaller ones, that each obey the laws of physics. This lends itself nicely to a realistic feel in a gunfight, as the terrain and environment turn to rubble and dust around you!Physics: Structures actually obey the laws of physics (mostly); if you blow up the base of a freestanding object, the rest crumbles (In the style of a 3d King Arthur's Gold).The Editors: This is where the game really shines! Look at the artwork the community has done in regards to characters. There are so many small details you can edit, you can let your imagination run wild!The map editor is also very detailed, allowing you to create huge structures, or vast fields. Were you a kid that liked playing with Legos and then destroying your masterpieces with as much ingenuity as you were legally allowed? That's the map editor in a nutshell :)You can then take these creations and share them online with other players in game, or via the forums. Which brings me to....Community: Small but active. Devs and Admins regularly interact on the forums, answering questions and giving feedback. You get the sense that they really are relying on the players to help them shape the game... unlike soooooo many other games on this Steam list.And then we get to the bad...Population: Is depressingly low. I've yet to see more than 10 people on a server. However, when you combine this with all of the above and the Early Access state of the game, there really isn't much you can complain about. IN some cases, playing may even become secondary to creating maps and characters!"
76561197978423729,Recommended,263060,11226162,"Posted: 13 July, 2014",all,Floyd ^A^,"Seriuosly, there is NO other game like this. Similar but nowhere near the playabilityof this game. The map editor is quite powerful with the ability to easily lay down long linesof blocks at a time it's a breeze to build the biggest structures. I've made maps in 2 to 3 hours time whichhave plenty of content and play well. There really is nothing more satisfying  than making your own mapthen loading it onto the servers to play with other BlockStormers. If you like FPS games you'lllike this one alot."
,Not Recommended,263060,14589824,"Posted: 21 February, 2015",all,[duk] Ḡґø☺ṽƴ,"""Players don't need to be publicly criticized and harassed because of their unthoughtful behaviour, no matter how bad it is. Hacking isn't as serious as something like depression.""New review: 2/22/2015This game is a lot of fun to play.There are a few problems though. One is the teamkilling mechanism - you are sure to die to your teammates at least 2 or 3 times a match, thanks to all of the explosions. And if you accidentally kill your teammates 3 times in a game, they can vote to kick you. (which actually happens a lot)Two: the moderators and developers use permanent bans. And if you disagree with their policies, they will lock or delete threads. I took snapshots of the relevant posts with Archive.today, in case they delete the threads. Moderators and developers speak down to all players on the forum with a condescending tone. The best you can do is hope the moderators and developers leave you alone. To that effect, I recommend that you do not join the Blockstorm forums.Page 1:https://archive.today/F7eITPage 2:https://archive.today/Bk8xpPage 3:https://archive.today/xUqqYPage 4:https://archive.today/A2ps3Page 5:https://archive.today/1IoS6Page 6:https://archive.today/Fc3vPModerators threaten to delete another thread regarding ban policy:https://archive.today/HdY8cUpdate 2/24/2015: When accused by the community of cheating, the moderators assume you are guilty until proven innocent. Note that most modern justice systems assume you are innocent until proven guilty - therefore, Blockstorm has a medieval moderating system.Here are the statements by Keys of the Eighth Dawn, one of the game's server moderators, in the forum chat box, proving that Blockstorm uses a ""guilty until proven innocent"" medieval justice system:koted: Oh, and btw, Noubexxx received a temp ban.koted: Three days.koted: Yeah, but if he does it again, it will be doubled.koted: But as told him, the community thinks he cheats. So until he proves otherwise, he cheats, period.And here is a forum discussion in which players accuse Noubexxx of cheating, with no concrete evidence:https://archive.today/TVlbWIn medieval justice systems, the accused were often tortured without a trial, and had to undergo an ""ordeal"" to prove their innocence to their community. The same system is used in Blockstorm, where the player is presumed guilty, may be banned without a trial, and must similarly prove their innocence.http://www.historylearningsite.co.uk/medieval_law_and_order.htmSee also: ""Nobody expects the Spanish Inquisition!""https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7WJXHY2OXGEKeys of the Eighth Dawn, a staff moderator, claims to support free speech, but locks threads in the forums to silence debate:https://archive.today/lqXY7""Ok, I'm locking it""https://archive.today/V1pMGUpdate 3/2/2015: Good news! A player who had been previously banned with no evidence, has now been unbanned, pending concrete evidence of cheating.The bad news: on page 2, another player requests that a moderator lock a thread, to halt further free speech or debate.https://archive.today/YoGEYhttps://archive.today/BTlhHUpdate 3/2/2015:They did lock the thread on page 2.https://archive.today/DOAtiUpdate 3/2/2015:The moderators have turned 180 degrees. They have now decided that cheaters are rare, due to the anti cheat system, and changed the policy to require concrete evidence before a player can be banned for cheating. In particular, Noubexxx has been found innocent of cheating, even after he was already punished with a 3 day ban.https://archive.today/90B1aUpdate 3/5/2015:A Blockstorm moderator wrote a reply to this review... and unsurprisingly, they immediately locked the thread, so no one can reply! Brilliant. :)https://archive.today/KzZPcUpdate 3/6/2015:Blockstorm moderator Exenoxx comments below that Noubexx was banned automatically by players for being rude, rather than banned by a moderator for cheating. If that's true, why did Keys of the Eighth Dawn list Noubexx on this Blockstorm forum page as banned for ""Cheating: aimbot, no recoil;"" ?https://archive.today/2IeYz#selection-625.2-408.146Update 3/7/2015:Blockstorm moderator Exenoxx unlocked one of the threads. Exenoxx claims players are ""targetting"" the moderators. So I guess a review on the way moderators and developers treat players is ""targetting"" them? I guess free speech must be a lot worse than insulting players, accusing players, banning players without evidence, and locking threads.https://archive.today/EgNWTUpdate 4/24/2015:A Blockstorm player wrote a very thoughtful argument against the ""report players"" forum, and how it could lead to cyberbullying.https://archive.is/Bxr2oA gem in the post above:""Players don't need to be publicly criticized and harassed because of their unthoughtful behaviour, no matter how bad it is. Hacking isn't as serious as something like depression.""Update to review on 10/20/2015:I was banned from the community forums for joking that this game is dead. It's funny how touchy the moderators are. But I think it has an element of truth, now that I think about it. Lately, when I log in to play this game, all the servers are empty. (and there are over 20 servers!) There are only about 6 hours a day where a server fills above 5 players. Not only that, but since the game is multiplayer only, you can't really play when no one else is online. If you want to play this game, you need to be willing to schedule your time around when other people are online. Average number of players online at any given time is less than 10 - so the elite players end up just dominating the small match sizes. And, of course, if you dare to mention that the game has very few players online, you can expect a ban. After all, if you tell other people there aren't many players, they might not buy the game, and the creators will make even less money than they are making now, selling so few copies.Update to review on 10/24/2015:From the chatango on the Blockstorm website:1: I was totally for Pro's temp ban and not perma and got called an alt-account as well2: haha2: pro soldier must be very entreprenurial2: plot twist: we are both actually pro soldier, and he's schizophrenic1: :o2: :O loominati confirmUpdate to review on 10/25/2015:Supposedly I was banned from Blockstorm's Steam discussions for ""necroposting."" I just looked at the posts in question. The oldest ""dead"" thread was only 2 weeks old, which is still relatively recent given Blockstorm's community size, and the second oldest was only 3 days old. The real reason they banned me was because they didn't like my opinions on those topics - namely, for criticizing the game's activity, and criticizing the clans (such as the administrator clan UNIT). Also, they could have warned me before banning. This is exactly the overly harsh moderation I was talking about in my review, and I will continue to criticize you, your game, and your moderators, regardless of how many times you ban me or censor me.I'm surprised they only banned me for 7 days to be honest - in the past, they would lock threads permanently if I expressed unpopular opinions. We will see what happens if I criticize Blockstorm or the moderators again when my ban expires.Once again, I'll point out I was banned not for cussing someone out, or for calling someone names, but because I said clans are stupid, and that the game has low activity compared to other FPSes. My ban is censorship, plain and simple.Update to review on 10/26/2015:Exenoxx recently claimed via chat that ""we are not like that anymore"" and their policies have changed. However, someone recently contacted me over Steam to say they have been banned from the game permanently, starting a few months ago.I implore the reader to draw his or her own conclusions."
