,Recommended,263060,17244646,"Posted: 26 July, 2015",all,Finnbro,"I recently picked up this game on sale, and I have to say that it is one of the best value purchases I've ever made on Steam.  I highly enjoy both Minecraft and CS:GO, so it is a natural fit.  I find the actual gun combat to be only so-so; it seems some guns are more usable than others and the motion isn't exactly fluid, but overall it is fun and adequate given the other stellar features of this game.The customization options in this game are what truly won me over.  The Steam Workshop already has TONS of custom skins for characters, guns, melee weapons, tools, and NPC skins, along with custom maps and an in-depth map editor somewhat similar to Minecraft.  The character and gun customization tools are wonderfully in-depth and easy to pick up.  I made a few of my own custom guns and had a blast doing so, considering you can change both the shape and colors of the guns to fit your look.The built-in maps are solid, and if you enjoy Minecraft resource packs there's a lot of really nice scenery and building inspiration in this game.  Obviously you can make your own maps, and host your own servers with those maps, which I find to be really cool.  Some maps are designed just for singleplayer or co-op with NPC and item placements.  The scenarios that you can create in this game have the potential to be fairly interesting once you get a grasp of the mechanics.Overall, this is a really solid bang for your buck title.  Even at the regular price it's a great value purchase.  There are a lot of Minecraft wannabe games out there, but this one really deserves a look if you're a First Person Shooter fan.  Since its a new game, there may be updates to hope for in the future, but it's already a very enjoyable experience in its current state."
