,Recommended,263060,12184081,"Posted: 22 September, 2014",all,|WEP|Grim_Reaper,"Im just going to post a basic little first thoughts review.The game isn't bad. It's like a nice more advanced version of Ace of Spades in my opinion. Gameplay is simple. Run, shoot, hide, build. It's not very fast paced. It's fairly relaxed and there is no singleplayer with AI etc.The amount of weapons you have to choose from is alright. Nothing really fancy. But the weapons do their job. I'd say there is room for more unique weapons though if the developer is interested in adding more ""out there"" kind of weapons.I'd say despite this being an early access game. It is looking fairly polished with the content so far. There aren't many gamemodes as of yet. But there are apparently more coming soon.I do not know the plans for the game once it's finished (this is an early access review) But I do feel this game lacks in content that could increase fun in gameplay. Be it an improvement to the way the world/maps are affected by the player(s), maybe a singleplayer with monsters or something with little singleplayer missions (nothing fancy mind you, or perhaps some more unique weapons/items. But most important, I'd enjoy it more if there was a sprinting ability and being able to prone. Not just crouch.Now, onto the verdect.Do I recommend this game?My answer is if you love(d) Ace of Spades and similar games. Then I'd say this game may just be something you'll enjoy. So yes. I'd recommend it.Is it worth it's price of $12 right now?I'd say it just meets my requirements for a yes at this point.All in all. A nice little game. If you're unsure whether to get it. I would suggest watching some gameplay videos first before purchasing."
