76561198087942218,Recommended,263060,12175096,"Posted: 21 September, 2014",all,Snoot Salamander,"Blockstorm is not like those other ""Minecraft with guns"" games. It revolves around this editor, thing, which can be used to create your character, create a level, and you can make ANYTHING. Minecraft revolves around crafting, mining, and some combat. This revolves around combt, creativity, adrenaline, and excitement. In Call of Duty, you could run around and shoot people, but you could not create your character from the skeleton out. in this, you can. you can make a fat man, thin man, short man, tall man, disfigured man, AND you can base your characters off of other characters. While playing earlier, i saw a guy running buy with a Finn the Human model from Adventure Time. And then, i saw a guy who's model was Patrick, from SpongeBob SquarePants.The possibilities are quite endless. I STRONGLY recommend that you purchase Blockstorm. The graphics are AMAZING, if you are pondering that. The graphics, shading, textures, movements, weapons, and editors are not like your typical ""Minecraft with guns indie game"" they are, in fact, Call of Duty level graphics, in cubic form. But, one of my favorite features of the game, is that the world is destructible. You can shoot blocks to destroy them. Pretty fantastic, if I do say so myself. Anywho, I highly suggest you purchase Blockstorm"
