76561198074867492,Not Recommended,263060,25980770,"Posted: 11 October, 2016",all,Dragon Force,"TitleBlockstormDeveloperGhostShark GamesPublisherIndieGalaRelease6 June 2014, available on Steam in 21 May 2015Graphics3DGenreVoxel FPSPrice€4,99Rating3/10The game.BlockStormwas developed by Italian developer GhostShark Games. They have previously released a racing game calledGoscurryfor PC and a puzzle game calledJelly All Starsfor iOS mobile devices.Blockstormwas published by IndieGala, a company that always gives us the best indie games at great prices.Gameplay.What is the basic formula behindBlockStorm? It’s simple, grab the blocky characters fromMinecraftand give them high caliber guns and explosives to shoot each other in highly moddable and destructable environments. Almost everything in this game is highly customizable: the characters and especially the maps. There are several game modes, including but not limited to Classic Deatmatch, Team Deathmatch, Capture The Flag and others.The controls are the classic FPS. It plays out similarly to old school arcade deathmatch FPS games likeQuakeorUnrealrather than to modern military shooters such asBattlefieldandCall Of Duty. There is no 360noscope or other shenanigans that requires superhuman abilities. Just regular running, shooting and jumping. And occasionally blowing up stuff. There is a sizable quantity of weapons to choose, ranging from pistols and submachineguns to semi-automatic rifles, assault rifles, light machineguns and rocket launchers.The weapons are horrible. Unbalanced. Currently, there are only RPG, LMG, MP5, AK, UZI, shotgun, sniper, rifle and handguns in which all of these have horrible sound effect and it makes you feel like you're using a card board gun made in China. The sniper and rocket launcher are useless. If your gun is automatic you win. The only populated servers are the ""DEMO"" servers witch feature only 4 maps. Map/Player skin creation is the only decent thing is this game.Character actions are basic and you are only limited to aim-shoot, run, crounch and jump. No sprinting, diving, or lying on the ground. If you want to playSuper Marioin 3D, this game is for you.Basically,Blockstormis a voxel FPS that has a wonderful system but with poor gameplay quality. Good concept but lack of polishing. I understand that the game community is not big yet and the devs do not have a large income from this game, but this is my honest impression of this game at its current state.Positive points. (+)Minecraftstyle with FPS.Customization.Very indepth character/weapon editor.Negative points. (-)No ingame tutorial on how things work/straight into gameplay.Unbalanced weapons.Matchmaking system could be better.The game don't have many players on the servers.Toxic playerbase (if the game is going to be an online only FPS, then someones experience with the game can be quite easily ruined when half of the current server they are on are spouting racial slurs and derogatory terms for certain groups)."
