,Not Recommended,263060,16752066,"Posted: 27 June, 2015",all,Grinny,"*Note, this is a review from the very narrow perspective of a new player. I'm saying what I see.Pro:This game is very fun. The idea is great and it's VERY enjoyable to be able to make your own skins for yourself and your weapons. That alone makes the money I spent worth it.There are plenty of game modes to choose from that all feel different. Every game mode has a different objective or approach to it and it actually is really enjoyable to bounce around to different modes.Con:Unless I'm crazy, the servers are very empty a lot of the time. Only 1 or 2 in any given timezone has players-even though there's like 5 or 6 servers total to choose from, and usually only one of those two is close to being full I've found.The sound design is horrible. You don't hear gunshots unless you're RIGHT UP NEXT TO THE PERSON THAT'S SHOOTING. The only time you ever hear a gun being shot at you is a slight ""whiff"" when bullets are close to you that's very quiet. In fact, a lot of the sounds are very quiet or nonexistent. Footsteps, damage sounds; the sound design in general just doesn't seem very well contrived at all.Verdict:At this point in time I can't in good conscience recommend the game. It's FUN, but rather empty and home to some pretty annoying design choices. Particularly regarding sound. 5/10"
