,Not Recommended,263060,29256766,Posted: 14 January,all,A Deep Commitment To Konata,"When I saw the blocky/voxel art style I was expecting something like Team Fortress 2 where you complete comical objectives and stuff, take like 20 bullets before dying, and blocky comic mischief.What I got was an Ace of Spades clone with advanced customization features. Nothing makes sense when you get killed by silent entities from across the map because the sound doesn't travel well enough. You don't even hear bullets hitting you half the time. Much less does anything explain the collision when digging trenches I got stuck at least 5 times in the same trench because my feet kept getting stuck or something. Stuff you shouldn't be able to dig through, you can dig through. Stuff you shouldn't be able to break, breaks.This game is 1-2 hit kills. Guns are bulky and don't shoot straight, even at close range, much less seldom aided by its ironsights feature. There are very few sound cues so you can only rely on your health bar to tell if you're taking damage. Zombies poke you to death.This game feels VERY unfinished. Its as if they had literally taken Ace of Spades, increased the model resolution of players. The guns don't shoot where you aim, there's little to tell if you're doing damage other than a thin bar above your target, and nothing makes sense.This feels like a beta. Not a all worth 5 dollars. I'd pay 99 cents for it because thats about all the enjoyment I got out of it, most of that $5 probably goes towards coding those editors. The editors and character/weapon/world customization are the only things they did right; its a shame its all to waste because the gameplay is nothing like you'd expect."
