,Not Recommended,263060,16842924,"Posted: 2 July, 2015",all,KardaKAX,"TL;DR at the bottom.Now, saying a game is bad and that I, personally, wouldn't reccomend it is two different things that people often get mixed up about.I don't have any major complaints about the game other than how it introduces new players.I mean, the gameplay is smooth, the animations are good (for what is there) and the fact that they have implemented an in-game skin customiser that has workshop compatability is something that more games need to be doing. The voxel system is something I loved since I first played Ace of Spades on one of the free weekends.However, I just can't understand how the game works.I understand the premess of the game with it's objective systems yet I have no idea how the gun play works, of which many games at least show you a tutorial of this. Sure, I can look this up from other users yet I do fee the game should have some responsability in that department.Also, I found that the choises for arnaments are very restricting. There were your base weapons (ARs, Shotguns, LMGs etc.) but that was it, really. I don't feel like I have as much freedom as some other games, which, as a user, I need to have to stay interested in the game. These also, to me, feel and move very clunky as well as the contraction time on crosshair. I personally think a few tweaks may be needed to make the guns feel like guns and not a lucile bat that sparks out bullets.The maps that I play in the quick-join seem to be very small, restricting and quite dull. Now, I don't have enough experince to see how it works propperly, yet, if these are the maps the devs have made, I don't think a tiny 3-room map with a few corridors is enough for a CTF, maybe a DM or a small TDM.TL;DR: I don't like the game for the gunplay, maps and how hard it is to get into, yet I do find the premess of the voxels and skin customisation very nice. It's a decent game, but, I can't say I like it."
