76561198055406889,Not Recommended,263060,13764292,"Posted: 1 January, 2015",all,SodOffShogun,"I will just begin with the positive side of this game.I do like some of the mechanics in this game, it might just be a personal preference however I find them as something that makes this game ever so slightly more challenging than just a click of the mouse, for example the sniper's scope sways slightly as you zoom in which I think makes it more challenging that just scoping in and just gunning everybody down. So It's nice to know that something is keeping the sniper rifle from being Over-Powered.Another substantially nice part about this game is the editors. Just to give a run-down of the editors you are allowed to edit and design your own in-game characters as well as maps to play on with your friends which I think is neat. You could say like it is an ever changing battlefield.Now for the negative side of thingsAs of writing this review I lost a good friend  of mine, Pro-Soldier. He was banned unreasonably and without a reason at the least which upset me very much. I don't know if this is just people disliking him for being the highest leveled person on the game or it just being some act that was so non-benevolent. I've asked multiple times to members of the UNiT clan whom of which contains a few moderators from my knowledge why Pro was banned and I have received no response since then, I don't know if they did not want to confront the issue, talk about it, or just plain were being ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥s though each one has the same possibility as the other.Hackers or at least exploiters; there are few however, the ones that do exist within the game do make it a pain. I'll say I've come across some people who somehow (I dont even know how) manage to spam the RPG and what I mean by that is that the can continuously launch Rockets non-stop, or at least in rapid succession. From what I know the RPG only has 1 Rocket that comes with it, so too see somebody not get a kill and pick up that persons backpack and launch a second RPG is very displeasing. Nonetheless I wouldnt say its the most major issue because you can typically just snipe them from across the map if you are good enough.I've personally come across a few bugs that I've tried addressing before but have been dismissed. One that I discovered is one where if you are underground in a tunnel lets say, if you place down a claymore or C4 and walk over it you clip through the ground and can see where every player is. I think this is just a simple bug that needs to be fixed  but It does get annoying seeing some people exploit this which becomes a pain in the @$$ when you are trying to have a legitimate game.Overall the community is alright. This isn't nescessarily a positive or negative but rather just an observation.Personally its not a suprise to me that from a Romance speaking and mediterranean country to expect a product like this where there is not industry about it.  Ubisoft however is a French games company, France is a Romance speaking and some what a meditteranean country, though France is different, France is situated and bordered around Germanic/Germanic language speaking countries where their economies are stronger. This is where the French get their influence from and out paces other Romance and mediterranean speaking countries i.e. Spain and Italy where there the most southern of all European countries and do not have an history in technical industry like producing video games even though in the past it seems to differ so.Nonetheless I have to sadly downvote this game for a few reasons but In some ways the game is entertaining and if this review is too long for you then buy the game!.69/10"
