,Recommended,263060,13194933,"Posted: 2 December, 2014",all,The Mortiest Morty,"For an early access I was skeptical, But it didn't take much more than the Title screen before I realized this game was trying hard to deveop itself at its own pace and POLISHed to boot.Shortly: Game plays like counter Strike. Not too serious, But not too twitch-shootery either. Features and gamemodes are still being added, And game rooms tend to be empty unless you join around your area's Prime times or before school hours.As I write this, There's CTF, DeathMatch, Team DeathMatch, Assault modes. Assault plays a bit like some form of land grab where the defending team must prevent the attacking team from occupying a specific zone or more for a certain amount of time.The controls and interfaces for the game itself and it's various editors were a little different at first, But with a little learning and some wikis I found htem extremely intuitive for working with Voxels, And the editor for making your own skins is top-notch. Nothing is more satisfying than making your own, Unique skin or map.Workshop integration launched recently too, And already is filling up with many quality prefabs, Maps and characters. So far for it's time, And the constant work and communication with the developers, This is promising to be the Well-made voxel shooter of the year if more players support this company.Try the demo, Albeit you are limited in weapon map and skin it's a good sample of the fun that can be had in this game.I would rate this 4/5 stars. And that's being picky about some features, But being an early access it could very well change the moment I hit 'POST' on this review..!"
