76561198101966249,Recommended,263060,32442596,Posted: 15 June,all,The Gentleman,"This game is Awesome.I bought this game when it was only $0.89 on steam, but for $2.99 its worth every penny.The game runs very well even on toasters, although, in high populated servers you can generally expect a lower frame rate, though its manageable enough.Secondly, this game gives you complete control over each of your weapons and character models, so if you want to customize it to fit whatever design you have, you can do that. If you have the time, and patience you can a really awesome skin, or really awesome weapon. I've got nearly 20 different skins for my weapons, and more when I feel like it. For what it's worth, its probably one of the best purchases I've made.My main gripes with the game are the melee hit boxes, as I frequently miss people I should have hit, and hit people who I should have missed, although the hitbox is based off the default knife skin, and not so much as whatever skin you have on your weapon. Additionally the damage in the game is very inconsistant, the rifle normally kills people in 1-3 shots(if you hit the head, 3 anywhere but the head, and 2 if the first shot is a body shot and second a head) although there are times when it takes a whole magazine to kill them, and all I get are hit markers. The sniper is also a big concern with the game, as there seems to be a bit of a delay from when you flick your scope onto an enemy and aim to compensate. there will be times when I scope in, over or undershoot my aim, and when I go to move the scope there's about a half to one second delay before you reaim in otherwords, unless you aim right where there at and scope in perfectly, sniping is very hard.Additionally, when you want to make a new weapon from scratch, you can't break it all the way down, you can only break it down to essentially it's skeleton.(the exeption being the knife that you can make it into whatever you want.) this gets infuriating if you have a very clever design but you are limited to game's coding of the skeleton, which is understandable, but this in turn makes you get even more creative about your problem.Overall though, I would still say that this game is worth its price, as you can create just about anything in the game, the only limits are what your own imagination can come up with."
